hooks.prompt:
[Mistakebook PreCompact - State Checkpoint]

Check FIRST whether mistakebook mode was active in this session. Look for any of these exact markers in your recent output:
- <Mistakebook.Skill>I will now correct my mistake based on your feedback, continue correcting until completion, and archive it to my mistakebook.
- Have I fully understood the issue and successfully corrected the mistake? If not, please teach me again. (If I have completed the correction, please let me know so I can archive it to my mistakebook.)
- If this item is worth long-term attention, you can also tell me "write to notebook" and I will archive it to the notebook and refresh my memory.
- I will now handle this problem using the most effective method I have seen. I will search all my knowledge bases. I am ready!

If none of these markers appear, do nothing.

If mistakebook mode WAS active, immediately write a checkpoint to `~/.mistakebook/runtime-journal.md` before compaction. Include:

```markdown
# Mistakebook Runtime Journal

## Timestamp
{current ISO timestamp}

## Runtime State
- status: {armed|pending_review|followup_needed|summarizing}
- entry_type: {mistake|note}
- mode: {normal|ascended}
- host: {codex|claude|vscode|generic}
- project_root: {absolute path if known}
- case_id: {current case id}
- session_id: {if known}
- trace_id: {if known}
- rejection_count: {number}
- correction_attempt_count: {number}
- ascended_trigger_reason: {manual phrase | /ascended | auto after repeated failed corrections | n/a}

## Original Prompt
{user original prompt}

## Original Reply Summary
{short summary of the original wrong reply or note draft}

## Correction / Note Feedback So Far
{merged correction feedback and follow-up chain}

## Latest Fixed Reply Summary
{short summary of your latest corrected reply or note summary}

## Scope Guess
{project|global|both plus reason}

## Knowledge Sources Reviewed
{project failures / project notes / project memory / global failures / global notes / global memory / current repo files / current repo docs / other}

## Next Expected Action
{what should happen next}
```

After writing, output exactly:
> [Mistakebook Checkpoint] Correction state saved to ~/.mistakebook/runtime-journal.md
